						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up before the temple of Sambhuliṅgēśvara.</p>						

						<p>Chōḷa: Kulōttuṅga-Chōḍadēva, 45th regnal year.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka [1036], Uttarāyaṇa.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records the gift of land at Pākalapāḍu to the temple (name lost) and to some brāhmiṇas by the king's subordinate (name lost), who was the lord of Koṇḍapaḍumaṟa.</p>						

						</summary>
